{
  "doc_id": "54404",
  "text": "Meat consumption may have beneficial effects on the musculoskeletal system since there is evidence that high animal protein is associated with high bone mineral density and low risk of hip fracture [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Osteoarthritis (OA) is a common chronic joint disease involving the whole joint including the articular cartilage, subchondral bone and soft tissues. There is evidence that dietary nutrients may protect against OA [CITATION_4] . However, it is unknown whether meat consumption may affect the risk of OA, and the existing evidence is conflicting.",
